26) In JIRA workflow, is it possible to transition an issue back to its previous status?\par
\par
Practically, it is not possible to transition an issue back to its previous status.  However, you can use \ldblquote onhold\rdblquote  feature to transition an issue back to its previous status. Here are the steps,\par
\par
In workflow, Create a global transition to the \lquote On Hold\rquote  status.\par
Now from \lquote On Hold\rquote  status create another transition to every other status you want to come back to\par
Since the transition names cannot be the same, just add a blank space at the end of it.\par
Now you don\rquote t want the status transition from the \lquote On Hold\rquote  and \lquote Done\rquote  to \lquote On Hold\rquote  So you will hide the other status \ldblquote On Hold\rdblquote  by adding the value field condition on the global transition.\par
27) Mention what is the role of Validators in JIRA?\par
\par
The Validators in JIRA checks that any input made to the transition is valid before the transition is performed.  If a validator fails, the issue will not progress to the destination status of the transition.\par
\par
